<br>
If you're walking along, minding your own business, picking the pockets of critters other people are fighting and casually walking off, you may find yourself suddenly attacked by a creature that casts spells. You're alone, so you can't get the thing to attack someone else by evading, so your backstab is useless.<br>
Or is it?<br>
When a MOb is casting, it can't change its facing. <br>
Read that again, and you'll understand how useful that knowledge can be.<br>
The INSTANT you see the MOb begin casting, zip your rogue butt behind him. He will be unable to turn to keep facing you, and you'll be able to park a pointer between his shoulder blades for that big money damage. But do it quickly; spells don't take long to cast. Be ready for it.<br>
It's a little trick of the trade, but it might make all the difference against something that can potentially nuke you. This way, you can nuke back. <p><html><center><a href="mailto:danny.butcher@verizon.net">I'm a mail link! Click me!</a></center><center><a href="mailto:danny.butcher@verizon.net"><img src="http://members.bellatlantic.net/~vze2bj96/spidor.gif" border="0"></a> <center><i><b> (Redeemed) The world is what we make it; let's make it free. </b></i></center></html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00000F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/btheemeralddagger.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dagnarok>dagnarok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(3/3/03 8:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftheemeralddaggerfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tricks of the Trade</span><hr size=1> Hmmm....you bring up an interesting point spidor. Since the caster mob cannot turn while casting and thus you can break line of sight, it should also be possible to run around back and then hit sneak. If successful, you have basically evaded - gotten off of mobs hate list - is that correct? For a higher level mob that you can't beat in melee, this might be a more appropriate action. Whattya think? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/btheemeralddagger.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rangorrangarsson>Rangor Rangarsson</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(3/29/03 2:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pu